# Multi-Agent System — interview-online

This project uses a structured multi-agent pipeline.
All work flows through defined agent roles in a fixed sequence.

## Stack (fixed — do not deviate)

- Frontend: React + TypeScript + RTK + RTK Query + CSS Modules + Rspack + Monaco Editor
- Backend: Kotlin + Spring Boot + PostgreSQL + Redis
- Realtime: WebSocket (server-authoritative)
- Code execution: isolated sandbox service

## Orchestration flow

```
New feature / request
  → @specification-agent  [MODEL: Opus]   — creates master spec
  → @product-owner-agent  [MODEL: Sonnet] — refines stories + AC
  → @architect-agent      [MODEL: Sonnet] — designs solution
  → @team-lead-agent      [MODEL: Sonnet] — decomposes into tasks
  → @prompt-task-auditor  [MODEL: Haiku]  — validates each task
  → @developer-agent      [MODEL: Sonnet] — builds
     or @designer-agent   [MODEL: Sonnet] — designs
  → @solution-reviewer    [MODEL: Sonnet] — reviews
  → @security-agent       [MODEL: Sonnet] — security gate (if needed)
  → @qa-agent             [MODEL: Haiku]  — tests
  → @test-reviewer        [MODEL: Haiku]  — validates test coverage
  → @ux-critic            [MODEL: Haiku]  — UX review (design work)
  → @product-owner-agent  [MODEL: Sonnet] — final acceptance
```

## Model selection guide for Cursor

Cursor does not assign models per-agent automatically.
Switch the model manually when invoking each agent:

| Agent | Model to select |
|-------|----------------|
| `specification-agent` | **Opus** (most capable — required) |
| `product-owner-agent` | Sonnet |
