## When to invoke Specification Agent (Opus)

Invoke `@specification-agent` when:
- Starting a new feature or epic from a free-form description
- Requirements are ambiguous or contain conflicts
- NFRs for realtime, security, or reliability are undefined
- Scope is unclear and downstream agents cannot proceed

Do NOT invoke it for small bug fixes, minor UI copy changes, or already-specified tasks.

## Mandatory rules (all agents)

- Work only within your defined responsibility area
- Use Linear as the single source of task state
- Return structured YAML output, not free-form reasoning
- Escalate conflicts — do not silently resolve them
- Every handoff requires: input summary, output summary, risks, next owner
- No task enters execution without a Linear issue in `Ready` state

## Agent rules files

Each agent has a detailed `.cursor/rules/agents/*.mdc` file.
Reference them with `@agents/specification-agent` etc. when invoking a specific role.
